# Helm dependency tarballs - fetched fresh via `helm dependency update`,
# which scripts/provision-cluster.sh already runs as part of setting up any
# cluster this chart deploys to. Originally committed deliberately (matching
# podiumd-infra's own convention) for offline reproducibility without that
# step - reversed once provision-cluster.sh existed to run it automatically,
# and once this 3.87MB tarball turned out to be the direct root cause of a
# real bug: Helm's release record embeds the entire resolved chart including
# this dependency, exceeding Kubernetes' hardcoded 3MB API request-size
# limit and forcing `helm install` to be abandoned for `helm template |
# kubectl apply` in the first place (see plan.md's step 4 notes). Chart.lock
# stays committed - it's a small text file (name/version/repository/digest
# only), genuinely useful for pinning without any of the tarball's downsides.
charts/*.tgz

# OS
.DS_Store

# Python (tests/)
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.pytest_cache/
